HEADWORD: H. M. S.
<hw>H. M. S.</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A prefix used in the names of
British warships, meaning <sig>His Majesty's Ship</sig> or <sig>Her
Majesty's Ship</sig>; <as>as, <ex>H. M. S.</ex> Pinafore</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
